# Frontend (Vite + React + React Router SPA)

Render projections of the server snapshot (REQ-15.1). The Node session service is the source of truth (ADR-1).

## WebSocket and snapshot

- Use `useSessionWs` for the single WebSocket per show (ADR-2). Do not open a second socket from a component or page.
- Treat `snapshot` as read-only. Never mutate it locally to "look ahead" — send an intent and wait for the next `snapshot` broadcast.
- Mirror the server `SessionSnapshot` exactly in `src/sessionTypes.ts`. When the backend adds a field, add it here too.

## Sending intents

- Always send `{ type, payload }` via `send` from `useSessionWs` (it queues until `OPEN` and after `join`).
- The client never decides legality — phase transitions, score changes, role permissions are all server-validated. Surface `lastError` from `useSessionWs` when the server rejects.

## Role-gated UI (REQ-7, REQ-14)

- `/admin` is the Host route (REQ-14.2). Gate Host-only controls behind `getHostSecret()` + `role === "host"`. Hide them entirely from other roles, do not just disable.
- During main rounds, do not render Player-level controls for `role === "spectator"`. Mini-game inputs follow the same gating (`role === "player"` for donations, etc.).

## Routing (ADR-3, SPA)

- Routes live in `App.tsx` via React Router `<Route>`. Deep links such as `/admin` must work — never rely on server-rendered HTML.
- Read `showId` from `URLSearchParams` once with `useMemo`, default to `"default"`.

## Component conventions

- Functional components and hooks only — no class components, no default-export-only files for shared components.
- Import via the `@/` alias for `src/*` (configured in `vite.config.ts` + `tsconfig.json`).
- Type `Phase`, `Role`, `SessionSnapshot`, `RoundBoardRuntime` from `@/sessionTypes` instead of restating shapes inline.
- Strict TypeScript: no `any`, no untyped state. Narrow union members with `phase.kind === ...` switches.

## Styles

- `src/index.css` is an `@import` manifest only — never add rules to it. Append rules to the matching partial in `src/styles/`.
- Partials (in load order, which is the cascade order): `base.css`, `show-shell.css`, `players-panel.css`, `show-columns.css`, `lobby-slideshow.css`, `quiz-board.css`, `modal.css`, `question-modal.css`, `forms.css`, `theme-icon-editor.css`, `quiz-board-cells.css`, `login.css`, `chat-panel.css`, `game-header.css`, `layout-modifiers.css`.
- Pick the partial whose name matches the component/feature you are styling. Create a new partial (and add it to the manifest) only when the rules belong to a clearly distinct topic with no existing home.
- Do not reorder existing `@import` lines without a reason — order is the global cascade. New partials go before `layout-modifiers.css` so page-level overrides stay last.
- Co-locate `@keyframes` with the rule that uses them, in the same partial.
- Inline styles only for ad-hoc layout already established in the codebase.
